#Text=Pays de la Loire
#Text=The Pays de la Loire is an extensive region of north-western
#Text=France to the west and south-west of Paris , separated from it by the adjoining region of Centre-Val de Loire with which it shares many affinities .
#Text=Both regions border on the Loire Valley and host famous châteaux .

#Text=The Pays de la Loire is somewhat more diverse , however , and has a long coastline along the Atlantic Ocean , forming the northern part of the Bay of Biscay , within the area known as the Vendée .

#Text=Talk
#Text=The language here is much the same as the rest of France , with more northern than southern influences due to the influences from Paris , and basic French will be easily understood .
#Text=By car
#Text=From Paris , the A11 autoroute runs to Le Mans and onto Angers and Nantes .
#Text=The A28 runs from Normandy from the north and Tours from the south to Le Mans .
#Text=Also from Tours , the A85 links to Angers .
#Text=From the south , the A83 comes from Niort and runs up through Vendée to Nantes .
#Text=From Brittany , there are no autoroutes into the region , however , the N165 , N137 and N157 run from Morbihan , Rennes ( south and west ) respectively .
#Text=By train
#Text=Le Mans is in the western branch of the LGV Atlantique line from Paris Montparnasse ( commonly known as the TGV service ) .
#Text=Standard mainline track then runs onward to Angers and Nantes .

#Text=The city also has rail connections to Caen to the N and to Tours to the S , to Rennes ( via Laval ) to the W and to Chartres to the E. Nantes has rail connections to the N to Rennes and S to La Rochelle as well as to Angers then Le Mans then Paris by TGV .
#Text=Angers additionally has rail connection to Le Mans to Tours and to Nantes .
#Text=Saumur has rail connections to Nantes as well as Tours and Angers then Paris by TGV .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Pays de la Loire is served by two commercial airports :
#Text=Nantes Atlantique
#Text=The main airport in the region has good transport links from the center of Nantes and is 10 minuets off of the ring road .
#Text=If has flights to the Caribbean , Africa , North America and of course , other European airports .
#Text=Angers –
#Text=Loire
#Text=The only commercial flights go to and come from London City Airport and are run by British Airways .
#Text=There are three car rental companies operating at the airport : Europcar , Enterprise and Avis .
#Text=The car park is completely free and has direct access to the terminal .
#Text=Also on the airfield is an aviation museum which is worth a visit if you 're into that sort of thing .
#Text=Get around
#Text=The region has a good rail network , with the majority of services operated by TER Pays de la Loire .
#Text=Loire Valley
#Text=Loire Valley .
#Text=The Loire Valley is the 3rd touristic destination in France .
#Text=It is the largest site in France ever inscribed on UNESCO 's World Heritage List under the heading of Living Cultural Landscapes .
#Text=Kings , artists and famous authors , seduced by the Loire , were many to take up residence on the banks of the " Royal River " .
#Text=You can enjoy Renaissance Chateaux , medieval fortresses , historical gardens or unspoiled landscapes by car , by foot , by bicycle or on board a bareg .
#Text=Wine , music , litterature , art , sailing , and food are also part of this legacy .

#Text=Puy du Fou historical theme park .
#Text=With over 1,5 million visitors a year , this is one of the most popular attractions in the whole of France .
#Text=It has 5 main attractions , including a birds of prey show and a Roman style gladiator fight and a number of smaller ones .
#Text=All spectacles are in French , but for the main ones electronic translators are available .

#Text=During peak season , there 's a regular " Cinescene " , a huge show depicting 700 years of history in the region , but you 'll need to book separate tickets for it . € 31 for adults , kids € 22 .
#Text=Booking in advance will give a 3 euro discount. .
